I watched only the first two episodes, after which I had to stop. My reason? The upskirts were just too much. I have no problem with nudity or sexualisation in media, but I feel that HOTD's treatment of this often contentious issue completely missed the mark;
In any reasonable quality film or show, nothing is accidental. Especially in the case of anime, where everything is drawn (or computer generated, or whatever), every aspect of every frame is there because someone put it there. This should seem obvious. The problem with HOTD's frequent upskirt shots is that they are completely gratuitous. They serve no purpose and existonly for their own sake. These sorts of shots do have a place in film-making and anime, but they would usually be used to expand the feel of the world (usually to represent the sleazier undertones of humanity, think sin city or similar), or to further the exploration of a character (maybe to present vulnerability, or to expand a promiscuous character trait). The upskirts and jiggling breasts in HOTD do not mean anything. 


Of course, a point could be made that not every anime has to be 'smart'. Some exist for pure entertainment and are shallow by nature. In such a light, sexualisation doesn't need to be meaningful. Which brings me to my second point, frequency;


We're not talking about an upskirt here and there, the sexual undertones and suggestive camera angles are pretty much through the whole show. HOTD feels like it's trying to pay homage to the classic zombie/teen slasher flicks of yesteryear, and those were known for often frequent nudity. The difference is that those films considered 'frequent nudity' to be 3-4 scenes in a whole 90 minute film, not 20 upskirts in a 20 minute episode. It became so frequent in the first two episodes alone that it was distracting from the main action and detracted considerably from the feel and flow of the episodes.


HOTD insults women by presenting them as sexual objects in completely unreasonable situations for such a presentation. It insults men by assuming that's what they want to see. And finally, it's a kick in the teeth of anime being seen as anything approaching artistic. It's material like this that has attached such a social stigma to watching anime in the first place.

I went in expecting a popcorn slasher about zombies. I was expecting violence, sexualisation and one dimensional characters, but it was just too much. If you don't mind an upskirt shot literally once a minute, maybe there's a cool show to be found here. Maybe I'm missing something, but to me it was the anime equivalent of a teenager drawing dicks in his notebook.

.:: Story ::. 
The story in Highschool of the Dead is pretty straightforward and obvious.  It revolves around a world that's been quickly corrupted by zombies.  A group of teenagers band together to escape the school and survive the apocalypse.  The story was for the most part, good, but I wouldn't say it was the greatest. The first few episodes were interesting, but things start straying away the further you travel into the series. Overall, I give the plot a score of 6/10 {Fair} 
.:: Artwork ::. 
I really love the character designs and art styles used in HSOTD. The animation isreally good. It's  vivid in color and detailed. Also the fighting scenes  are done in a creative matter, so it adds it's own personal flair that sets it apart from other shows that have zombies.  for artwork I give it a 9/10 {Great!}  


.:: Sound ::.


Both the opening and ending themes are very good.  I found myself singing a long to them :]. The background music is also nice, it's not too distracting or overused and it fits the mood, as well as well timed sound effects. I watched both sub & dubbed versions (I'm not picky about dubs), I find both versions to have good voice acting. I think the English dubbed voices actually suited the characters more then the Japanese dubs, but I like both. I have nothing to complain about.  I give sound & music a score of 9/10 {Great!} 


.:: Characters ::. 


There's a couple of interesting characters introduced in High School of the Dead, but for the most part there isn't much character development throughout the series. I love many of the characters, although many of the girls are bitchy, I give them props for having some spunk! That's what I love about them. I give this a score of 6/10 {Fair}


.:: Enjoyment ::. 


I really enjoyed watching the series. However, this Anime contains a lot of fanservice moments.  There is a lot of boobs bouncing and pantyshots.  Since I'm a girl myself, honestly fanservice never really bothered me. But in HSOTD it can get pretty distracting since they put heavy empthasis on this. It shows up A LOT.  At times it can be a real mood killer. I wouldn't have minded much I'd they didn't give us an overload.  In a way, large boobs jiggling and skirts flying up during fights gives off a realistic feel. 


.:: Overall ::. 


My overall score for this Anime is 7/10 {Good}
